history.text: Hi, how are you?  Have you seen the movie Inception?
Hi, Yes, I have seen Inception!
Oh fabulous!  What a great movie.  It stars Leonardo DiCaprio as Dom Cobb.  He's a professional thief.  As you clearly know.  It got great reviews on Rotten Tomatoes and IMDB.
It should get great reviews, it was really entertaining!
Critics have described it as a "wildly ingenious chess game", which I would say is quite accurate.
I think the addition of Tom Hardy and Ellen Page and Joseph Gordon-Levitt also helpped to strengthen the cast and make it an overall hit, don't you?
Yes, I agree they are all very good actors. I really like Joseph Gordon-Levitt.
Yes, he is great.  Do you like Christopher Nolan movies (the director) in general, or have you seen any of his other movies?
I'm not sure, what else is he known for?
I am not sure either.  I thought the overall plot of Inception was so wildly creative and it kept me intrigued throughout.
yeah, you're right. I really like creative movies that I haven't seen a story-line like before.
what did you think of the ending?
well, I thought it was a decent ending.  My favorite scene however was when Fischer was abducted, and they took him to that warehouse.  I thought that was so fascinating.
Did you like the ending?
That scene was intense. What did you find so fascinating about the warehouse specifically?

I loved the idea of putting the dying dreamer into "limbo", a world where you had infinite subconsciousness.  Such an interesting and abstract idea.  The risk of not recalling the fact that you're in a dream?  It intrigued me.
It clearly seemed like a key scene of the movie, though.  It was suspenseful too in spite of the whole deeper dream thing.
Almost like being trapped in the dream, was it really a dream, it messes with perception of reality.
Yeaah exactly, that's what I liked about it.  I like when movies mess with the perception of reality and question what is real.  This movie was great at that
The idea of dreamscapes being created and described as "mazes" is also interesting to me, what do you think

Agreed! It makes me nervous of being trapped in my mind, i
t seems to vivid and as though it's probable. Would you see it again?
Yeah I would because it's been a long time since I saw it!  Would you?
yeah! I'd like to introduce more people to it too!

Do you remember the scene where Cobb and Mai spent fifty years in a dream constucting a world from their own memories that they shared?  I thought that was interesting too, like what if we could do that?
And then remember the aftermath of that, where Mal thought she was still dreaming when she actually woke up, then killed herself, framed Cobb, who was then facing a murder charge?
50 years in a dream seems like a prison sentence.Yeah, I remember. Maybe I'd like it if it was a really pleasant dream.
yeah seriously.  and it was actually only a few hours.  Yeah I know right?  I was still kinda unsure in the ending when he joined his kids in that garden, was he dreaming or was it real?
That is the scary part, not knowing dream land from reality and being harmed by yourself because of not knowing which side of the line you're on.
Yeah exactly!  Like what happened to them.  It is a bit scary.  Perhaps staying in reality is best.
Have we met the requirements of this HIT?
exactly, I wasn't sure either.
I feel that we have.
me too
i think 12 are required]
okay have a great afternoon! enjoy Inception if you re watch.  Yeah I think so, an d I believe we've met that.
have a great day friend
